The paper discusses techniques for training energy-based models (EBMs) on high-dimensional data domains such as ImageNet and CIFAR-10, which are typically studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The paper also highlights the unique capabilities of implicit generation, which is a topic of interest in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) community. Additionally, the paper applies EBMs to robotic hand trajectories, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) category. Finally, the paper achieves state-of-the-art results in various tasks, including out-of-distribution classification and adversarially robust classification, which are relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) community. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.RO.
